b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Teixeira vs. Bader</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 28</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> that was held on September 4, 2013, at <a href="/wiki/Mineirinho" title="Mineirinho">Mineirinho Arena</a> in <a href="/wiki/Belo_Horizonte" title="Belo Horizonte">Belo Horizonte</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A bout between <a href="/wiki/Raphael_Assun%C3%A7%C3%A3o" title="Raphael Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o">Raphael Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o</a> and <a href="/wiki/T.J._Dillashaw" title="T.J. Dillashaw">T.J. Dillashaw</a> was briefly linked to this event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>  However, the pairing was delayed and will take place at a later event this year due to a minor medical issue for Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Godofredo_Pepey" title="Godofredo Pepey">Godofredo Pepey</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Sam_Sicilia" title="Sam Sicilia">Sam Sicilia</a> at the event.  However, Pepey pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Felipe_Arantes" title="Felipe Arantes">Felipe Arantes</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>  Then, on August 7, Sicilia also pulled out and was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Kevin_Souza" title="Kevin Souza">Kevin Souza</a>, the former <a href="/wiki/Jungle_Fight" title="Jungle Fight">Jungle Fight</a> featherweight champion.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SiciliaOut_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-SiciliaOut-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Kenny_Robertson" title="Kenny Robertson">Kenny Robertson</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Jo%C3%A3o_Zeferino" title="Jo\xc3\xa3o Zeferino">Jo\xc3\xa3o Zeferino</a> at this event. However, Robertson pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by UFC promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Elias_Silv%C3%A9rio" title="Elias Silv\xc3\xa9rio">Elias Silv\xc3\xa9rio</a>, the former <a href="/wiki/Jungle_Fight" title="Jungle Fight">Jungle Fight</a> welterweight champion.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-RobertsonOut_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-RobertsonOut-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Johnny_Bedford" title="Johnny Bedford">Johnny Bedford</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Viana_(fighter)" title="Hugo Viana (fighter)">Hugo Viana</a> at this event. However, Bedford pulled out of the bout citing an injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup> Viana was then briefly scheduled to face UFC newcomer <a href="/wiki/Wilson_Reis" title="Wilson Reis">Wilson Reis</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>  Then just days before the event, Viana also pulled out of the bout citing an injury and the bout was cancelled.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Marcelo_Guimar%C3%A3es" title="Marcelo Guimar\xc3\xa3es">Marcelo Guimar\xc3\xa3es</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Keith_Wisniewski" title="Keith Wisniewski">Keith Wisniewski</a> at this event. However, Guimar\xc3\xa3es pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by UFC promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Ivan_Jorge" title="Ivan Jorge">Ivan Jorge</a>, the former <a href="/wiki/Jungle_Fight" title="Jungle Fight">Jungle Fight</a> lightweight champion.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Guimaresinjured_11-0"><a href="#cite_note-Guimaresinjured-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>]'